cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 

- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the physical and logical topology of the Internet and associated performance in the Indian Ocean Area. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper may discuss security concerns related to the Internet infrastructure in the region. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper may involve the analysis of network traces and the development of a tool to extract useful information. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper may discuss the impact of the Internet infrastructure on social networks in the region. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper may discuss the societal implications of the lack of Internet access and quality in the Indian Ocean Area.
